==English==

===Etymology===
From {{L.}} ''[[ambientem]]''

===Adjective===
'''ambient'''

# [[encompass|Encompass]]ing on all sides; [[surrounding]]; [[encircling]]; [[enveloping]].
#: ''A cup of tea eventually cools to the '''ambient''' temperature.''
#: ''“'''Ambient''' Intelligence” represents an intelligent environment of computing nodes.''
# {{music}} Slow and [[peaceful]]; [[atmospheric]].

===Noun===
'''ambient'''

# Something that [[surround]]s.
# {{music}} A type of modern music which [[incorporate]]s elements of [[various]] musical styles, and creates a [[relaxing]] and [[peaceful]] [[atmosphere]].

====Synonyms====
*(''music'') [[ambient music]], [[chillout]]

